# Urfael remote bridges (Telegram / Discord / Slack / iMessage). Copy to ~/.claude/urfael/bridge.env and `chmod 600`. NEVER commit.
#
# Remote access is OPT-IN and SANDBOXED: every remote message is forced into the restricted 'untrusted'
# profile (no bypassPermissions even with URFAEL_YOLO, no computer-use, read/search/web/notes only), and
# ONLY the single owner id below is ever answered — every other sender is dropped before the brain sees it.
# Leave a section blank to disable that channel. With this file absent, bridges and phone notifications
# are simply off.

# --- Telegram (works on Node 18+) ---
# 1. Create a bot: message @BotFather -> /newbot -> copy the token.
# 2. Get your numeric chat id: message @userinfobot, or open https://api.telegram.org/bot<token>/getUpdates
#    after you DM your bot, and read message.chat.id.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_OWNER_CHAT_ID=

# --- Discord (needs Node 22+ for the built-in WebSocket) ---
# 1. Create an application + bot at https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Under the bot, ENABLE the "MESSAGE CONTENT INTENT" (privileged) so it can read your DMs.
# 3. Invite the bot, then DM it. Get your numeric user id: Settings -> Advanced -> Developer Mode,
#    then right-click your name -> Copy User ID.
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
DISCORD_OWNER_USER_ID=

# --- Slack (Socket Mode — needs Node 22+ for the built-in WebSocket) ---
# 1. Create an app at https://api.slack.com/apps (from scratch).
# 2. Enable Socket Mode (Settings -> Socket Mode). That generates an app-level token (xapp-…) with the
#    connections:write scope -> that is SLACK_APP_TOKEN.
# 3. Under "OAuth & Permissions", add Bot Token Scopes: chat:write, im:history, im:read. Install the app to
#    your workspace and copy the Bot User OAuth Token (xoxb-…) -> SLACK_BOT_TOKEN.
# 4. Under "Event Subscriptions" (Socket Mode), subscribe to the bot event: message.im. Reinstall if prompted.
# 5. Get your own user id: click your profile -> "Copy member ID" (U…), or any user-id helper -> SLACK_OWNER_USER_ID.
#    Then DM the app. Only that one user id is ever answered; everyone else is dropped before the brain.
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_OWNER_USER_ID=

# --- iMessage (macOS ONLY, best-effort — REQUIRES Full Disk Access) ---
# Reads ~/Library/Messages/chat.db read-only and replies via the Messages app over AppleScript. The process
# that runs the bridge MUST have Full Disk Access (System Settings -> Privacy & Security -> Full Disk Access);
# add your terminal/launchd runner there or the bridge exits with a clear message. Needs the sqlite3 CLI.
# IMESSAGE_OWNER_HANDLE is the EXACT handle as it appears in Messages: a phone in +E.164 form (e.g. +15551234567)
# or the Apple ID email. Only inbound messages from this one handle are ever read or answered.
# IMESSAGE_POLL_SECS is how often to check for new messages (default 4).
IMESSAGE_OWNER_HANDLE=
IMESSAGE_POLL_SECS=4
